'''Harbin Veterinary Research Institute''' (HVRI) is a Chinese biological research institute located in [[Harbin]], China. It is under the supervision of the [[Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences]] (CAAS).
HVRI was created in 1948 and is the first veterinary medicine research institute in China.
In 2013 the HVRI has come to the public attention due to the controversies surrounding its research on [[H5N1]] and [[H1N1]] viruses.<ref>{{cite web|author=jobs |url=http://www.nature.com/news/scientists-create-hybrid-flu-that-can-go-airborne-1.12925 |title=Scientists create hybrid flu that can go airborne : Nature News & Comment |publisher=Nature.com |date=2013-05-02 |accessdate=2013-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Steve Connor |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/appalling-irresponsibility-senior-scientists-attack-chinese-researchers-for-creating-new-strains-of-influenza-virus-in-veterinary-laboratory-8601658.html |title='Appalling irresponsibility': Senior scientists attack Chinese researchers for creating new strains of influenza virus in veterinary laboratory - Science - News |publisher=The Independent |date=2013-05-02 |accessdate=2013-05-06}}</ref>
