The '''Ferrater Mora Oxford Centre for Animal Ethics''' was founded in [[England]] in 2006 by [[Andrew Linzey]], a member of the Faculty of Theology at the [[University of Oxford]], though the centre is not affiliated with the University.<ref>[http://www.oxfordanimalethics.com/about-the-centre/aims-vision/ OCfAE: Aims and Visions]</ref> Other founding fellows were Ara Paul Barsam, Mark H. Bernstein, Scott Cowdell, Susan Pigott, and [[Mark Rowlands]]. The centre is named after the Spanish/Catalan philosopher, [[José Ferrater Mora]].<ref name=centre/> or Josep Ferrater i Mora (in Catalan).
The centre promotes ethical concern for animals through academic study and public debate, and aims to create a global association of academics willing to advance the ethical case for animals.<ref name=centre/> To that end, it publishes an academic journal, the ''Journal of Animal Ethics'', jointly with the [[University of Illinois]].<ref>Bingham, John. [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/howaboutthat/8479391/Calling-animals-pets-is-insulting-academics-claim.html "Calling animals 'pets' is insulting, academics claim"], ''The Daily Telegraph'', 28 April 2011.</ref> It has also established an animal ethics series with Palgrave MacMillan.<ref>[http://www.palgrave.com/products/series.aspx?s=pmaes "The Palgrave Macmillan Animal Ethics Series"], Palgrave Macmillan, accessed 25 May 2012.</ref> The centre held an International Conference on the Relationship between Animal Abuse and Human Violence at [[Keble College, Oxford]] in 2007.<ref>Linzey, Andrew. ''The Link Between Animal Abuse and Human Violence''. Sussex Academic Press, 2009, p. 9.</ref>
Linzey is the centre's director. Advisers include [[Stephen R. L. Clark]], [[Roger Crisp]], [[Roger Fouts]], [[Robert Garner]], [[A. C. Grayling]], [[Hilda Kean]], [[Jeffrey Moussaieff Masson]], [[Bernard Rollin]] and [[Steven M. Wise]]. Honorary fellows include [[J. M. Coetzee]].<ref name=centre>[http://www.oxfordanimalethics.com/about-the-centre/welcome/ "Welcome"], [http://www.oxfordanimalethics.com/who-we-are/advisers/ "Advisers"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120605043457/http://www.oxfordanimalethics.com/who-we-are/advisers/ |date=2012-06-05 }}, and [http://www.oxfordanimalethics.com/who-we-are/honorary-fellows/ "Honorary Fellows"], Oxford Centre for Animal Ethics, accessed 25 May 2012.</ref>
The Centre is based at 91 [[Iffley Road]] in [[Oxford]].
